+1

An inexpensive "secure" (which may mean limited in funcationality) end
user hardware router with a minimum 3 outgoing and one incoming connection
is required; to create a non centralised mesh network of some sort.

Then, the predominant usage model of the internet needs to be shifted to
"people using this non centralized end user controlled mesh network".

Then some protocols layered on top of this.

Again: If you don't own it, you don't control it, if your don't control
it, it --will-- be used against you.

It's a minimum 20 year plan, but it is the only option before us.

